@node Manual Installation
@section Manual Installation

Clone the Git repository.  In your Emacs initialization file, add entries to the @code{load-path} variable; load Nael; then optionally, configure it.

@lisp
;; git clone https://codeberg.org/mekeor/nael ~/path/to/nael

(add-to-list 'load-path "~/path/to/nael/nael")
;; (add-to-list 'load-path "~/path/to/nael/nael-lsp")
;; (add-to-list 'load-path "~/path/to/nael/nael-markdown")

(require 'nael)
;; (require 'nael-lsp)
;; (require 'nael-markdown)
@end lisp

@node Installation via @code{package-vc}
@section Installation via @code{package-vc}

Since version 29 from 2023, Emacs ships with @code{package-vc} which teaches the default package manager how to install packages from version-controlled source repositories.  Keep in mind to regularly upgrade thus installed packages with @code{package-vc-upgrade} and @code{package-vc-upgrade-all} commands.

(Unfortunately, both @code{package-vc} based approaches will byte-compile the Elisp source files of all packages inside Nael's Git repository.  Just ignore the resulting compilation warnings.)

